## <a id="3-0-1"></a> v3.0.1
**Release Date: September 8, 2020**

### Features
New features and changes in this release:

<p class="note warning"><strong>Warning</strong>: As of v3.0.1 of <%= vars.product_short %>,
  2&nbsp;CPU cores and 2&nbsp;GB of memory are required for each VM on your foundation.
  Not allocating enough resources can cause VMs to be unresponsive.
  For more information, see <a href="./install.html#acknowledge">Installing and Configuring</a>

* **Adds a mandatory field to inform and acknowledge the minimum resource requirements for VMs.**
* **Adds the ability to enable a Hardware Enforcement check during Pre-start**. This ensures the minimum requirements for resources are met for each VM (2&nbsp;CPU cores and 2&nbsp;GB of memory).
* Updates golang dependency to v1.14 for both Linux and Windows

### Security Fixes
This release includes the following security fix:
* High [CVE-2019-15961](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2019-15961):
  A vulnerability in the email parsing module Clam AntiVirus (ClamAV) Software versions
  0.102.0, 0.101.4 and prior could allow an unauthenticated,
  remote attacker to cause a denial of service condition on an affected device.

